column53:
[['Step' 'Activity']
 ['1'
  'Prepare the standard spiked blank acidified rabbit plasma as follows: 
To a microtiter tube, add: 
• 
180 µL of blank acidified rabbit plasma 
• 
20 µL of the appropriate MK-0011 / L-000000009 working standard solution']
 ['2' 'Cap the microtiter tubes and mix well.  Remove any air bubbles.']
 ['3'
  'Add to a 96-round deep well extraction plate (1.2 mL) the following: 
For Calibration Standards: 
• 
20 µL of appropriate acidified rabbit plasma standards (from Step 2 above)  
• 
20 µL of IS working standard solution 
For Blank Samples: 
• 
20 µL of appropriate blank acidified rabbit plasma 
• 
20 µL of ACN/H2O [50/50] with 0.1% FA 
For Standard 0 (IS Blank Sample): 
• 
20 µL of appropriate blank acidified rabbit plasma 
• 
20 µL of IS working standard solution 
For Unknown and Quality Control Samples*: 
• 
Appropriate volume of unknown sample or matrix QC (and blank acidified rabbit 
plasma, if needed) for a final volume of 20 µL 
• 
20 µL of IS working standard solution']
 ['4' 'Add 200 µL of crash solvent (MeOH) to the extraction plate.']
 ['5' 'Seal the deep well extraction plate with appropriate plate mat.']
 ['6' 'Vortex for 2 minutes using a multi-tube vortexer at Speed 4.']
 ['7' 'Centrifuge the plate at 4000 rpm for 5 minutes at 10ºC.']
 ['8'
  'Transfer 80 µL of supernatant to a new 96-round deep well extraction plate (1.2 mL).']
 ['9' 'Dilute the supernatant with 120 µL of H2O with 0.1% FA.']
 ['10'
  'Seal the deep well collection plate with appropriate storage mat.']
 ['11' 'Vortex for 2 minutes using a multi-tube vortexer at Speed 4.']
 ['12' 'Centrifuge the plate at 4000 RPM for 1 minutes at 10ºC.']
 ['13'
  'Place the deep well plate in the autosampler and inject appropriate volume.']]
